Package com.enh.lmsclient

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AppConfig
    This class represents the configuration for the LMS client application.
    ApplyForLeave
    This class represents the functionality for applying for leave in the LMS client application.
    ApproveOrRejectLeave
    This class provides functionality for approving or rejecting leave requests by a manager in the LMS client application.
    EmployeeLogin
    This class provides the functionality for employee login in the LMS client application.
    EmployeeMenu
    This class provides a menu for employees in the LMS client application.
    GetAllEmployeesWithDetails
    This class provides the functionality to retrieve and display details of all employees.
    GetLeaveRequestesInTimePeriod
    This class provides the functionality to retrieve and display leave requests within a specific time period.
    GetLeavesDuringTimePeriod
    This class provides the functionality to retrieve and display leave requests within a specific time period.
    HrLogin
    This class provides HR (Human Resources) login functionality.
    HrMenu
    This class provides the HR (Human Resources) menu and related actions.
    ListEmployeesReportingToManager
    This class provides methods to list employees who report to a specific manager.
    ListLeaveRequestsForManager
    This class provides methods to list leave requests from employees reporting to a specific manager.
    Main
    The main class that provides a user interface to interact with the Leave Management System.
    ManagerLogin
    A class that provides manager login functionality for the Leave Management System.
    ManagerMenu
    A class that provides the menu and actions available to managers in the Leave Management System.
    SendEmail
    A class for sending emails using Gmail's SMTP server.
    ViewMyLeaves
    A class for viewing leave applications of a logged-in employee.
    ViewMyLeavesInTimePeriod
    A class for viewing leave applications of a logged-in employee within a specified time period.
